    <P style="font-family:Cambria, Cochin, Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size:170%;"><b>HEALTH BENEFITS OF CHICKEN BIRYANI</b></P>
    
    <dl>
        <dt><p style="font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;"><strong>1. PROTEIN-PACKED RECIPE</strong></p></dt>
        <dd><p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:130%;">Chicken and cashew nuts pack a punch with their protein content. Chicken's selenium antioxidant is a top-notch anti-aging and immune-boosting agent. Plus, it's a heart-friendly choice, reducing the risk of heart disease and strokes. Keep enjoying these nutritious foods for a healthy boost.</p></dd>
        <dt><p style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;"><strong>2. IT ASSISTS IN DIGESTION</strong></p></dt>
        <dd><p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:130%;">Chicken Biryani's spices like cumin, turmeric, and ginger aid digestion. Cumin boosts enzyme activity, turmeric prevents bloating, and ginger helps with gas release and digestion. Enjoy the tasty and tummy-friendly benefits of these spices in your meal.</p></dd>
        <dt><p style="font-family:Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;"><strong>3. THE ANTI-INFLAMMATORY PROPERTIES OF TURMERIC</strong></p></dt>
        <dd><p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:130%;">Turmeric reduces inflammation in the body. It has anti-inflammatory properties. Due to the presence of antioxidants, it aids in anti-aging. Turmeric is known to reduce the risk of brain diseases. Adding turmeric to Indian cuisine, especially with Chicken Biryani, reverses chronic heart conditions.</p></dd>
